                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d481">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Council/12–1845: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-12-18T13:00:00+03:00"
                            >December 18, 1945—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 18—7:40 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>4209. From the Secretary [of State to the Ambassador in Iran].<note n="23"
                        xml:id="d481fn23">The Secretary of State was in Moscow attending the
                        Conference of Foreign Ministers, December 16–26, 1945.</note> Reference
                    Tehran’s telegram to Moscow 339, December 15.<note n="24" xml:id="d481fn24">Same
                        as telegram 1132, December 15, 11 a.m., from Tehran, <ref target="#pg_496"
                            >p. 496</ref>.</note> You may tell Foreign Office withdrawal of troops
                    from Iran will be discussed here. You may also say informally it is improbable
                    any other Iranian question will be raised.</p>
                <p>I do not think it desirable to express my view regarding proposed visit to Moscow
                    of Iranian Prime and Foreign Ministers.</p>
                <p>To Tehran as 181; repeated Dept as 4209. [Byrnes.]</p>
                <closer>[<signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>]</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
